The Diners Club honoured the best winemakers in South Africa at the 39th-anniversary awards in Franschhoek. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa not only has world-class wine but some of the best winemakers too. Nitida Wines' Daniel Keulder scooped the 2019 Diners Club Winemaker of the year award. READ: Best winemakers in SA crowned Keulder won for his 2017 Nitida Pinot Noir. "It was quite unexpected for us. Durbanville is not really known for Pinot Noir in South Africa but we are very excited to have taken the trophy," he said. The Diners Club honoured the best winemakers in South Africa at the 39th anniversary awards in Franschhoek.